<h3 ALIGN="center"><!--mstheme--><font color="#CC3333"><font color="#FF0000">Hundreds of Muslims seek to recover <br>
usurped Mosque from Zionists</font><!--mstheme--></font></h3>

<p ALIGN="LEFT">Tabariya (Occupied Palestine) - </b>Hundreds of Palestinian Muslims from
the Galilee and the Triangle regions on 25 February performed the Friday congregational
prayer at the Albaher Mosque in Tabariya in northern Palestine, despite vociferous Jewish
protests against Muslims&#146; efforts to restore the site.</p>

<p ALIGN="LEFT">The Mosque itself, seized by Jewish gangs when Israel was created in 1948,
was sealed by the Jewish local authorities and at one point converted to a den for drug
addicts.</p>

<p ALIGN="LEFT">Moreover, the local authorities erected a fence to prevent Muslims from
praying in the Mosque.</p>

<p ALIGN="LEFT">However, hundreds of Muslims, mostly associated with the Islamic movement
in pre-1948 Palestine, succeeded in entering the Mosque.</p>

<p ALIGN="LEFT">The sermon speaker, Um Alfahem mayor Sheikh Ra&#146;ed Salah, called on
Muslims in Palestine to make utmost efforts to extricate the usurped Muslim holy places
from Zionist hands.</p>

<p ALIGN="LEFT">He pointed out that when somebody transgresses against Jewish holy places
in any part of the world, the Jews make a big outcry.</p>

<p ALIGN="LEFT">Sheikh Salah attacked those who converted the &#147;houses of God into
prostitution houses and dens of corruption and drug addictions.&#148;</p>

<p ALIGN="LEFT">He pointed out that Muslims in the Zionist regimes were subject to
religious persecution amid silent connivance on the part of the Israeli government.</p>

<p ALIGN="LEFT">However, Jews, he said, were giving themselves <i>carte blanche</i> to
take over and desecrate holy places belonging to others, particularly to Muslims.</p>

<p ALIGN="LEFT">While Muslims were performing the prayer, several Jewish thugs and
hoodlums assembled outside the site and began shouting anti-Islamic slogans.</p>

<p ALIGN="LEFT">However, the prayer went smoothly, as the Muslims refused to be provoked
by the provocateurs.</p>

<p ALIGN="LEFT">The Jewish State still controls over 200 mosques throughout Palestine and
refuses to reopen them to Muslims. </p>

