<h3 ALIGN="center"><!--mstheme--><font color="#CC3333"><font color="#FF0000">Hamas, Islamic Jihad, win in Hebron University
election</font><!--mstheme--></font></h3>

<p ALIGN="LEFT">Occupied Jerusalem </b>- Supporters of Hamas and the Islamic Jihad
organizations won the student election at Hebron University held on 28 February, receiving
22 seats out of the 41 seats that make up the college&#146;s student assembly.</p>

<p ALIGN="LEFT">According to HU Dean of Student Affairs, Musa Ajweh, the Islamic Bloc (the
student branch of Hamas) won 19 seats, while its junior sister, the Jama&#146;a Islamiyya
(Islamic Jihad) won three seats.</p>

<p ALIGN="LEFT">Fatah received 18 seats, and a coalition of leftist groups affiliated with
the Popular and Democratic fronts for the liberation of Palestine won two seats.</p>

<p ALIGN="LEFT">The results will thus enable Hamas and the Islamic Jihad to retain control
of the Council.</p>

<p ALIGN="LEFT">Hamas has been in control of HU&#146;s Student Council for the last ten
years.</p>

<p ALIGN="LEFT">Hamas completely or partially controls most student councils in
Palestinian universities and colleges.</p>

<p>Some observers believe student elections in the occupied territories by and large
reflect public opinion trends among Palestinians, especially in the absence of general and
municipal elections. </p>

