<h3 ALIGN="center"><!--mstheme--><font color="#CC3333"><font color="#FF0000">Prisoners at Askalon prison threaten a new hunger
strike</font><!--mstheme--></font></h3>

<p ALIGN="LEFT">Occupied Jerusalem </b>- Hundreds of political prisoners at the Askalon
(Eshkelon) prison have threatened to start a new, open-ended strike over their worsening
conditions.</p>

<p ALIGN="LEFT">According to human rights sources, the prisoners are being held in
solitary confinement and are subject to mounting maltreatment by Israeli prison
authorities.</p>

<p ALIGN="LEFT">The Palestinian HR organization (LAW) reported on 24 February that Israeli
mistreatment of the prisoners include, among other things, confining them to 170 cm-270 cm
cells with toilets and poor ventilation systems.</p>

<p ALIGN="LEFT">One particular detainee, Abdul Rahman Ghneimat, has been denied family
visits for a year and a half and in addition suffers from arthritis in the knees, for
which he had been prescribed medication.</p>

