<h3 ALIGN="center"><!--mstheme--><font color="#CC3333"><font color="#FF0000">Arafat: I could be assassinated if<br>
I gave more concessions to Israel</font><!--mstheme--></font></h3>

<p ALIGN="LEFT">Occupied Jerusalem -</b> Palestinian Authority Chairman Yasser Arafat
reportedly warned the United States and Israel that continued Israeli pressure on him for
more concessions on fundamental final status issues might lead some Palestinians to
assassinate him.</p>

<p ALIGN="LEFT">Palestinian sources close to Arafat on 23 February confided that the PLO
leader appealed to the U.S. administration to ask the Israeli Prime Minister Ehud Barak to
stop pressuring him for more concessions because &#147;this could endanger my life.&#148;</p>

<p ALIGN="LEFT">According to the sources, Arafat told the Americans recently that he
simply could not cross certain lines because doing so would be extremely unsafe and
dangerous for him.</p>

<p ALIGN="LEFT">The sources intimated that Arafat told the Americans that the problem
extends beyond Islamist organizations and other extremists to include many people within
Arafat&#146;s own Fatah organization who, he argued, would be furious if he caved in to
Israel on such fundamental issues as Jerusalem and the refugees.</p>

